  "local_port": 44590,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I study at Stanford?",
  "response": "Stanford University offers a wide variety of study locations across its expansive campus to cater to different preferences and needs. Whether you're looking for quiet environments, collaborative spaces, or access to resources, here are some popular places where you can study at Stanford:\n\n### **1. Libraries**\n\n- **Green Library (Poniter Stacks)**\n  - **Location:** 1585 El Camino Real\n  - **Features:** The primary library on campus, Green Library offers extensive collections, study rooms, computer access, and quiet areas ideal for individual study.\n\n- **Arrillaga Computer Science Library**\n  - **Location:** 353 Jane Stanford Way\n  - **Features:** Specialized for computer science students, this library provides resources, collaborative workspaces, and access to technological tools.\n\n- **William H. Bonsall Biomedical Library**\n  - **Location:** 450 Jane Stanford Way\n  - **Features:** Tailored for biomedical research, this library offers specialized resources and quiet study areas for students in related fields.\n\n### **2. Academic Buildings and Study Spaces**\n\n- **The Stanford Bookstore**\n  - **Location:** 720 Wingham Way\n  - **Features:** Besides books and merchandise, the bookstore area has comfortable seating and Wi-Fi, making it a convenient spot for studying.\n\n- **Stanford Student Union (SU)**\n  - **Location:** Baney Center, 105 Galvez Street\n  - **Features:** Offers various lounges, meeting rooms, and dining areas where students can study and collaborate.\n\n- **The Physics and Astronomy Library**\n  - **Location:** 371 Jane Stanford Way\n  - **Features:** Dedicated to physics and astronomy resources with quiet study areas and specialized collections.\n\n### **3. Outdoor Study Areas**\n\n- **Main Quad**\n  - **Features:** A historic and picturesque setting with ample space for outdoor studying. Ideal for those who enjoy studying in natural light and fresh air.\n\n- **Memorial Church and Surrounding Gardens**\n  - **Features:** Provides serene environments with beautiful gardens and quiet spots perfect for focused study sessions.\n\n- **Roble Hall Courtyard**\n  - **Features:** A tranquil outdoor space within the Humanities Quartets, suitable for group study or individual reading.\n\n### **4. Collaborative and Flexible Spaces**\n\n- **The Coupa Caf\u00e9**\n  - **Location:** Various on campus\n  - **Features:** Multiple locations around campus offering coffee and snacks, along with comfortable seating areas conducive to both individual and group study.\n\n- **Rodin Sculpture Garden**\n  - **Location:** Near the Cantor Arts Center\n  - **Features:** Offers a unique outdoor setting with art installations, ideal for creative thinking and relaxed study breaks.\n\n### **5. Specialized Centers**\n\n- **The Bing Concert Hall Study Areas**\n  - **Location:** Within the Bing Concert Hall\n  - **Features:** Quiet study spaces available outside of event times, offering a unique architectural environment.\n\n- **Graduate Student Center**\n  - **Location:** Across from Green Library\n  - **Features:** Dedicated spaces for graduate students, including lounges and study rooms equipped with necessary facilities.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Wi-Fi Access:** Most areas on campus offer free Wi-Fi, ensuring you can stay connected wherever you choose to study.\n- **Study Room Reservations:** Some libraries and academic buildings require reservations for group study rooms, so it's advisable to book in advance.\n- **Quiet vs. Collaborative:** Depending on your study style, Stanford provides both silent areas for focused work and collaborative spaces for group projects.\n\n### **Explore More**\n\nFor the most up-to-date information on study spaces, resources, and campus facilities, you can visit Stanford University's official [Campus Map](https://map.stanford.edu/) or the [Libraries Webpage](https://library.stanford.edu/). Additionally, reaching out to student services can provide personalized recommendations based on your specific needs.",
